  <div class="en">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 700 440" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="width:100%;height:auto;background:#111113;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);margin:20px 0">
    <text x="24" y="32" fill="#fafafa" font-size="16" font-weight="700" font-family="sans-serif">Traditional correspondent banking vs. Swift's shared ledger — what's actually 24/7</text>
    <text x="24" y="54" fill="#a1a1aa" font-size="13" font-family="sans-serif">The "ordering/validation" stage and the "final settlement" stage differ</text>
    <g font-family="sans-serif">
      <text x="24" y="90" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-weight="700">Traditional correspondent banking</text>
      <rect x="24" y="100" width="280" height="26" rx="4" fill="#22c55e" opacity="0.85"/>
      <rect x="304" y="100" width="112" height="26" rx="4" fill="#3f3f46"/>
      <rect x="416" y="100" width="280" height="26" rx="4" fill="#22c55e" opacity="0.85"/>
      <text x="360" y="118" fill="#e4e4e7" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12">Weekend: offline</text>
      <text x="24" y="150" fill="#71717a" font-size="12">Payments process only Mon-Fri business hours (paused nights/weekends)</text>
      <text x="24" y="188" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" font-weight="700">Swift shared ledger (tokenized commitments)</text>
      <rect x="24" y="198" width="672" height="26" rx="4" fill="#06b6d4" opacity="0.85"/>
      <text x="360" y="216" fill="#0a0a0a" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700">24/7 recording and validation of payment commitments (always on)</text>
      <text x="24" y="248" fill="#71717a" font-size="12">But the actual final transfer of funds behind it can still depend on each country's RTGS hours</text>
      <rect x="24" y="270" width="652" height="70" rx="9" fill="#1c1c1f" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="1.2"/>
      <text x="350" y="298" fill="#fbbf24" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="700">17 participating banks &#183; six continents</text>
      <text x="350" y="320" fill="#e4e4e7" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12">HSBC, Citi, UBS, DBS, Standard Chartered, Wells Fargo, BNP Paribas, MUFG, ANZ, BNY, and more</text>
      <rect x="24" y="356" width="652" height="56" rx="8" fill="#0e2a19" stroke="#22c55e" stroke-width="1.2"/>
      <text x="350" y="390" fill="#86efac" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="700">~9 months in development &#183; declared ready for initial use in July 2026</text>
    </g>
  </svg>
  <p style="font-size:11px;color:#52525b;margin-top:-10px">Based on CoinDesk, The Block, Swift's official announcement (July 9), and Ledger Insights. Actual final-settlement speed can vary by each country's RTGS operating hours.</p>
  </div>
